s. Programmers like to store things in powers of 2, right? Like 256. Look at the skill system. The rollover used to happen at what we call 3.6. Or 3.60. Or +2.60. If mods were stored like that, it makes sense that it would roll over after like +2.55 or +2.56. And it would also make more sense that so many of the actual values for puretone come out to about +1.75 rather than +1.7 or +1.8 and epic come out to about +.75.<br>
